  "prompt": "Why did Thor's hammer shake in the movie \u2018Avengers: Age of Ultron\u2019 when Captain America tried to lift it?",
  "response": "In \"Avengers: Age of Ultron,\" during a party scene, the Avengers take turns trying to lift Thor\u2019s hammer, Mjolnir. When it's Captain America's turn, the hammer slightly moves, which surprises Thor. This moment suggests that Steve Rogers is somewhat worthy of wielding Mjolnir, as the enchantment on the hammer allows only those who are deemed \"worthy\" to lift it. The subtle movement implies Cap\u2019s inherent qualities and moral integrity make him nearly worthy, foreshadowing future events in the MCU where he does eventually wield the hammer.",
